# Backend Integration — Walkthrough

## What Was Built

A full **Node.js + Express + MongoDB** backend connected to the React frontend.

---

## Backend Structure (`ayursutra-backend/`)

```
ayursutra-backend/
├── server.js              ← Express app entry point (port 5000)
├── .env                   ← MONGO_URI, JWT_SECRET config
├── config/db.js           ← MongoDB connection
├── middleware/auth.js     ← JWT verification + role guard
├── models/
│   ├── User.js            ← Patient / Doctor / Admin
│   ├── Appointment.js
│   ├── Therapy.js
│   ├── Invoice.js
│   └── Feedback.js
├── routes/
│   ├── auth.js            ← POST /login, /register, GET /me
│   ├── users.js           ← GET /patients, /doctors, PUT/DELETE /:id
│   ├── appointments.js    ← Full CRUD
│   ├── therapies.js       ← Full CRUD
│   ├── invoices.js        ← Full CRUD (doctor-owned)
│   └── feedback.js        ← CRUD + doctor reply
└── seedData.js            ← Demo data seeder
```

## Frontend Services (`src/services/`)

```
src/services/
├── api.js              ← Axios instance with JWT auto-attach
├── authService.js      ← login, register, logout, getMe
├── appointmentService.js
├── invoiceService.js
├── feedbackService.js
└── userService.js
```

**[AuthContext.jsx](file:///c:/Users/het22/Downloads/chatgpt%20react/ayursutra-react/src/context/AuthContext.jsx)** updated to call real API — login/register/logout all go through the backend.

