## How to Run

### Step 1 — Start MongoDB
Make sure MongoDB is running on your computer. If installed, it usually starts automatically. You can verify by searching "MongoDB" in Windows Services.

### Step 2 — Start the Backend (one-time seed, then start)
Open a **new terminal** and run:
```bash
cd "c:\Users\het22\Downloads\chatgpt react\ayursutra-backend"

# First time only — seed demo data:
node seedData.js

# Then start the server:
node server.js
```

You should see:
```
🚀 Ayursutra backend running on http://localhost:5000
✅ MongoDB Connected: 127.0.0.1
```

### Step 3 — Start the React Frontend
In the existing terminal (already running):
```bash
cd "c:\Users\het22\Downloads\chatgpt react\ayursutra-react"
npm run dev
```

### Step 4 — Open the App
Go to: **http://localhost:5173**

